# Spec-Driven Development Workflow

## Spec File Location
- Feature specs: `docs/specs/{feature-name}.md`
- Architecture specs: `docs/architecture/{component}.md`
- API specs: `docs/api/{endpoint-group}.md`

## Spec Template

```markdown
# Feature: [Name]

## Status: [Draft | Review | Approved | Implemented]

## Overview
Brief description of what this feature does and why.

## Requirements
- [ ] Functional requirement 1
- [ ] Functional requirement 2

## Data Model
Define new/modified entities with field types.

## API Endpoints
| Method | Path | Description | Auth |
|--------|------|-------------|------|
| POST | /api/v1/resource | Create new resource | Required |

## Acceptance Criteria
- Given [context], when [action], then [outcome]

## Out of Scope
What this feature explicitly does NOT cover.
```

## Workflow
1. **Write spec first** — before any code
2. **Review spec** — get approval from stakeholder/architect
3. **Compile to code** — use Agent mode to implement from spec
4. **Update spec** — if implementation reveals spec gaps, update spec FIRST, then code
5. **Spec is source of truth** — keep specs updated post-implementation for maintenance

## Rules
- Never start coding without a reviewed spec
- One spec per feature/component — no monolithic docs
- Use `// TODO: [spec-ref]` in code to link back to spec sections
- Specs are version-controlled alongside code
